flavorText: This Pokémon wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.
Whether it's due to a lack of moisture or a lack of nutrients, in Alola the mushrooms on Paras don't grow up quite right.
While young, they live together deep in the mountains, training themselves in how to fight with their scythes and move at high speeds.
It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.
An aggressive Pokémon that tackles anything it sees.
The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.
Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from another dimension.
The tips of its split tail quiver whenever it uses its psychic abilities to read its opponent's next move.
Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.
It flies by flapping its broad leaves and gives the sweet, delicious fruit around its neck to children.
